### ============================================
### URL Shortener — Sample HTTP Requests
### ============================================
### Use with: IntelliJ HTTP Client, VS Code REST Client, or httpYac
### ============================================

### --- Health Check ---
GET http://localhost:8080/health

### --- Actuator Health ---
GET http://localhost:8080/actuator/health

### --- Prometheus Metrics ---
GET http://localhost:8080/actuator/prometheus

### ============================================
### Authentication
### ============================================

### --- Register a new user ---
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "deepa",
  "password": "mypassword123"
}

### --- Login and get JWT token ---
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "deepa",
  "password": "mypassword123"
}

### --- Login with default admin ---
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### ============================================
### URL Operations
### ============================================
### Replace <token> with the JWT from /auth/login
### ============================================

### --- Create short URL (no auth required) ---
POST http://localhost:8080/api/urls
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://github.com/deepawasthi"
}

### --- Create short URL with custom code ---
POST http://localhost:8080/api/urls
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://example.com",
  "customCode": "demo"
}

### --- Create short URL with expiration ---
POST http://localhost:8080/api/urls
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://spring.io/projects/spring-boot",
  "expirationDate": "2026-12-31"
}

### --- Create short URL with custom code and expiration ---
POST http://localhost:8080/api/urls
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://kafka.apache.org",
  "customCode": "kafka",
  "expirationDate": "2026-12-31T23:59:59"
}

### --- List all URLs ---
GET http://localhost:8080/api/urls

### --- Search URLs ---
GET http://localhost:8080/api/urls/search?q=github

### --- Search URLs (another query) ---
GET http://localhost:8080/api/urls/search?q=example

### ============================================
### Redirect
### ============================================
### Replace <shortCode> with actual code from create response
### ============================================

### --- Redirect to original URL (returns 302) ---
GET http://localhost:8080/demo

### --- Check redirect with verbose output ---
# curl -v http://localhost:8080/demo

### ============================================
### Admin Dashboard
### ============================================

### --- Admin page (open in browser) ---
# http://localhost:8080/admin

### --- Admin API — list all URLs (with JWT) ---
GET http://localhost:8080/admin/urls
Authorization: Bearer <token>

### --- Admin API — list all URLs (no auth if ADMIN_TOKEN is empty) ---
GET http://localhost:8080/admin/urls

### ============================================
### Resilience & Rate Limiting
### ============================================

### --- Rapid-fire to test rate limiting (run in a loop) ---
# for i in $(seq 1 15); do
#   curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}\n" http://localhost:8080/demo
# done
### Expect: first 10 succeed (200/302), then 429 Too Many Requests

### ============================================
### Infrastructure Health
### ============================================

### --- PostgreSQL ---
# docker exec url-shortener-postgres-1 psql -U postgres -d urlshortener -c "SELECT count(*) FROM urls;"

### --- Redis ---
# docker exec url-shortener-redis-1 redis-cli ping

### --- Kafka topics ---
# docker exec url-shortener-kafka-1 /opt/kafka/bin/kafka-topics.sh --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --list

### --- Elasticsearch cluster health ---
# curl http://localhost:9200/_cluster/health?pretty

### --- Prometheus targets ---
# curl http://localhost:9090/api/v1/targets | python3 -m json.tool
